  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting access to Health Emergency in Displaced Population</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WHO is the lead agency for Health Cluster in the country and the agency of last resort aims to enable national, provincial authorities and local communities to more effectively address all public health emergencies through improving the emergency management capacity at all stages of an emergency management cycle preparedness and prevention, alert, response, transition and recovery. This project contributes towards decrease morbidity and mortality among people affected by conflict related trauma, displacement and deprived of emergency health services through the following actions &#x2028;
1- Establishment of three trauma centers in Logar (Baraki Barak DH), Wardak(provincial hospital of Maidanshar) and Samangan (provincial hospital of Aibak). The activity will complement the Mass Casualty Management planning, related training and provision of supplies that address the gaps of space, essential equipment and human resource for operationalize the selected hospitals to be fully functional as referral hospitals by 2019. The hospitals selected for the project are under high risk for conflict and facing inadequate support from the routine health allocation. The activity will be implemented in collaboration of EPHS implementing partner of the province. (WHO has already tested a similar project in Kunduz). &#x2028;

Taking into account the shortages in medicines and supplies that may be faced by health facilities in emergency settings, particularly in the overlooked area of non-communicable disease in displaced population.
2 -WHO&#x2019;s emergency health kit for Non-communicable diseases includes medical equipment and 22 essential medicines for chronic diseases such as hypertension, cardiac diseases, diabetes, chronic respiratory disease for population affected by displacement and conflict in four most affected provinces of Kandahar, Kunduz, Herat and Nangarhar.  These kits will be distributed in districts with the highest need of displaced population.

3 - Provision of trauma care and emergency primary health care in Kandahar Province - districts implemented by YHDO.  YHDO will implement trauma care, rehabilitation care and psycho-social support in Spinboldak, and establishing MHT in Spinboldak, Ghorak, Miyanshim, Nesh with emergency health programming.</narrative>
  </description>
